-- Colombia Stock Movers: Grupo Sura, Avianca Taca Holding Gain
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-03-09T21:33:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-09/colombia-stock-movers-grupo-aval-banco-de-bogota-avianca.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.4 percent to 15,040.23, while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  was little changed at 1,724.62.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA  (GRUPOSUR CB), the
parent company of  Colombia ’s largest bank, rose 0.3 percent to
31,480 pesos. The Medellin-based holding company said in a
filing yesterday that level 1 American depositary receipts for
its preferred, non-voting shares would start trading today.  Avianca Taca Holding SA (PFAVTA)  (PFAVTA CB), the owner of
Colombia’s largest airline, rose for a second day, climbing 2.7
percent to 4,250 pesos. The company yesterday said in a  filing 
that 2011 profit increased 221 percent from a year ago to 202
billion pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
